title: Frostbite Time Trial
description: 2nd Annual Frostbite Time Trial. Presented by Puget Sound Bicycle Racing and Wines of Washington.
course: 9 mile, flat course on Lowell-Snohomish River Rd. Course starts at   the County line and heads east along S-L River Rd towards Snohomish. Out and back course
registration:
Registration		Opens at 7:00am
Closes at 8:30am
Located at Rotary Park in Everett, WA (Lowell-Snohomish River Rd)

Cost 			$20 for all participants except juniors which are $10.
You can register on race day, or if you want an early start time, you may pre-register online or by mail, using a standard USCF event release form
http://www.usacycling.org/forms/rider_release.pdfMail to:

Puget Sound Bicycle Racing
114 S 202nd St
Des Moines WA 98198

Mail registration must be received by Wednesday, Feb 20th.
notes:
Other Notes The promoter reserves the right to change categories, places, and prize list
based on participation.
USCF rules enforced. This includes wearing a HELMET at ALL times when on your bike.

title: Ravensdale Cumberland Road Race
course: Held on rural roads of southeast King County, the course is a 28 mile constantly rolling loop with one short, 0.15 mile, steep, 20% plus, climb.  Road surface varies from excellent to poor.  New this year is a rolling climb finish just off the main course.
registration: Pre-registration via Active.com (fee applies) or mail completed USA Cycling Release Form with WSBA number marked on upper right along with a check for $ 25 payable to 4 Corners Cycling--Michael Kopp, to:  Michael Kopp, PO Box 873, Maple Valley, WA  98038.  Mail in pre-registration must be postmarked by April 30, 2008.  Day of race registration is $ 30.  Registration opens at 7:00 am for morning races and closes 20 minutes prior to category start time.  Registration opens at 11:30 am for afternoon races and close 20 minutes prior to category start time.
notes: Race notes and up to date race information is posted on the 2008 Ravensdale Cumberland Road Race Link at www.4cornerscycling.com  Categories may be combined if minimum field sizes are not met.
directions: From the intersection of SR 516, Kent Kangley Rd, and SR 169, Maple Valley Highway, proceed eastbound on Kent Kangley Rd approximately 2 miles to King County Ravensdale Park.

title: Capitol Criterium 2008
course: Scenic 0.7 mile technical course on and around the state Capitol campus with an uphill finish.  Map of the course is at www.cbcracing.org
registration: DAY OF RACE REGISTRATION ONLY (REGISTRATION CLOSES 30 MINUTES PRIOR TO THE SCHEDULED START TIME OF EACH RACE)
notes:
WSBA numbers will be used.  One-day licenses and rental numbers available, pin right side.  No cash prizes for senior championship categories (championship medals awarded only to Washington state residents).  Merchandise and cash prizes to Masters categories (see the race flyer at www.cbcracing.org for up to date prize listings).  One merchandise prize valued at $400 will be awarded in a raffle of all adult competitors, including the championship events. Junior boys and girls races (no prizes) Juniors Event: Event #4 in the Seattle Lance Armstrong Junior Race Series.  Junior age classifications, A (17-18), B (15-16), C (13-14), D (10-12).  Juniors will be combined but scored separately.  For more on junior racing and this series go to:  www.radracingnw.org
Pits:Free lap rule in effect/neutral support provided.  Field limits:  Cat 5 men/Cat 4 women 50 racers only (Promoter reserves right to combine fields if the number of racers is less than 20, in which case the field limit is 75).  All other categories limit 100 racers.  Approved helmets required.  All USCF rules in effect.  The minimum field for the Masters races is 10 riders in each race.  Otherwise fields will be combined.
directions: From I-5 North or South, take exit 105/105A and follow signs to the Capitol campus.  Parking is available in visitor lots on the back side of the campus.
